rking collaboratively with engineering to scope & phase delivery; working closely with Marketing/Sales/Support to deliver product to market and; writing of white papers, blogs and presentations. Key Responsibilities Include Possess deep & current market knowledge of the enterprise blockchain landscape including use cases across industries, customer adoption journeys and application development ecosystems As part of the product team, formulate, test and validate product/market fit hypotheses at a product and feature level. This includes deep, frequent engagement with customers globally to synthesize feature specifications and service offerings. Lead the product development process from inception to product delivery. Collaborate on PRDs, outline detailed customer use cases, and ensure the successful and timely shipment of VMware\u2019s blockchain products. Work in cross functional Agile teams combining Development, UX, QE and end-to-end solutions to deliver product to market. Analyze and evaluate complementary and competitive products, technologies, and solutions. Required Skills 5+ years product management or equivalent experience on a complex and technical software project of significant scope with 10+ years of work experience in technology industry or function Deep understanding of the application stacks enterprises deploy today, and the tradeoffs available to improve scale and availability of apps. Foundational understanding of the blockchain ecosystem, including competitors, partners, and technology solutions. Strong desire and ability to connect with customers, understand their challenges, and solve problems Strong familiarity with agile software development practices with the ability to collaborate with engineering leads on requirements definition, design and prioritization Strategic thinking and ability to present solutions to senior level and executive audiences, both internal and external Experience taking early stage products from concept through early go-to-market, and working in an ambiguous, complex, and rapidly changing environment. Strong communication skills: verbal, written and content presentation Preferred Skills Demonstrated experience with pre and post product/market fit activities in a product lifecycle including positioning, validating hypotheses, pivoting and scaling. Experience with solutions design for enterprise customers Ability to think and act fast to drive cross-functional alignment and execution in new areas with tight timelines A confident presenter who is comfortable leading face to face customer meetings and presenting to small-medium size audiences. Bachelor\u2019s Degree in an Engineering or related technology field or equivalent experience. MBA desired. What You\u2019ll Get Opportunities for you to work in a strong innovation culture alongside teams consistently leading the markets they are in, and competing against the best software companies there are Challenging, and engaging projects that will help change the landscape of corporate IT for the better. An authentic career path with a support cast that will help you along your journey Attractive compensation package with competitive salary, flexible bonus scheme, and long-term incentives Healthy work environment with company sponsored medical insurance programs, sport activities, and open communication Work-life balance tailored to your needs, paid vacation, paid sick leave, team events VMware Company Overview: VMware, we believe that software has the power to unlock new opportunities for people and our planet. We look beyond the barriers of compromise to engineer new ways to make technologies work together seamlessly. Our cloud, mobility, and security software form a flexible, consistent digital foundation for securely delivering the apps, services and experiences that are transforming business innovation around the globe. At the core of what we do are our people who deeply value execution, passion, integrity, customers, and community. Sh